  - 400: description "Invalid table compaction request", content text/plain, example "Invalid option combination: Can not use split-output here".
- The method also enforces validation logic (e.g., returning 400 for invalid option combinations) but those are reflected via the 400 response documented above.

I included only the Operation fields needed to represent the request body and the documented responses (summary, operationId, requestBody, responses) and expressed the CompactRequest schema inline using the JSON property names as they are serialized. No additional top-level fields were added.

